So, South Africa have managed to get the 7 wickets they needed when they started this session in a little less than two hours. However, they have let India score quite freely which has seen the lead go over 300 and we believe, the visitors have enough to consider them as heavy favorites to win this game.

OUT! BOWLED! It's all over! Marco Jansen bowls this on a length, on middle. Mohammed Siraj backs away again and looks to cut it but misses it altogether. The ball shatters the stumps and Jansen gets his fourth wicket of the innings. This has been a good fightback by South Africa but the lead for India is 304 and that is a formidable score on this pitch. India finish with 174 in this second innings and South Africa need 305 to win this game now.
Commentary.Howout: b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: A short ball, on the body. Jasprit Bumrah goes for the pull, but manages to get an under-edge onto his pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and a single is taken.
FOUR! Nicely played by Bumrah!  Back of a length, around off. Bumrah stays on the back foot and pushes it behind square on the off side. Gets it in the gap and a boundary towards third man.
Play and a miss again! A full ball, outside off. Siraj swings his blade again but misses.
Back of a length on off. Siraj makes room again and looks to hit it away but misses again.
A fuller delivery outside off. Siraj makes room and looks to get a bat on it but misses.
Back of a length, on off. Siraj backs away and looks to hit it towards the on side but misses.
Mohammed Siraj comes out to the middle now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one goes down and Rabada gets his fourth wicket. Back of a length, on middle. Shami looks to work it away towards the on side but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and flies towards third slip. Wiaan Mulder there takes a fine catch and India lose their ninth wicket. The lead is healthy for India but South Africa are chipping in with wickets here.
Commentary.Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, on middle. Shami blocks it out towards the on side.
A full ball, outside off. Bumrah blocks it out towards the off side.
Short ball on middle this time. Bumrah looks to pull but misses. Good short ball by Jansen.
A short ball on off. Bumrah goes for the pull shot but misses.
Edged but safe! A short ball, down the leg side. Mohammed Shami goes for the pull, gets a slight edge to the keeper. Quinton de Kock puts in a dive but fails to get there.
Fuller this time, outside off. Mohammed Shami pushes this to cover.
Short ball, outside off. Mohammed Shami gets beaten on the outside edge.
Rabada serves a fuller one, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah lofts it over covers for a brace. Bumrah gets off the mark with that.
Length, on middle. Bumrah blocks it out.
Swing and a miss! A length ball, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah looks to defend that but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Jasprit Bumrah comes to the crease now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Rishabh Pant departs and this is a big wicket for South Africa as he was adding some valuable runs and that too in quick time. He looks to continue his agressive approach. Steps down the track again. Rabada was probably expecting that and surprises him with back-to-back bumpers. This one has extra bounce in it and is also a tad wide outside off. Pant initially looks to pull but then tries to bail out as he realises he won't be getting on top of the bounce. It goes off the toe-end towards mid on. Ngidi takes an easy catch by moving to his left. A good innings by Pant. He has surely done his job.
Commentary.Howout: c Lungi Ngidi b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Another boundary for Pant! Short ball on off. Pant gets back and pulls it hard towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. Pant is playing a good cameo here.
Back of a length, on off. Pant punches this off the back foot through covers and gets a couple. Another one which he connects with the middle of the blade.
On a length, on off. Shami defends this off the back foot.

Ohh... Brilliant fiedling by Bavuma. On a length, on off. Pant pushes it towards covers and sets off for a single. Bavuma there runs in picks the ball and fires in a throw at the bowler's end but misses. A single taken in the end.
On a length, outside off. Pant leaves it alone.

FOUR! Trademark one-handed shot from Pant! A length ball, on off. Pant skips down the track and smashes it inside out over covers for a boundary. His one hand came off while playing the shot but it dosen't matter.
FOUR! Valuable runs for India! Back of a length, on leg. Pant clips it fine towards long leg for a boundary.
Mulder starts with a back-of-a-length delivery on off after drinks. Pant defends this off the back foot onto the turf.

DRINKS! South Africa are ruling this session so far, they have managed to grab vital wickets here. But India would not mind that, they have got a healthy lead of 281 runs, and with Rishabh Pant still at the crease, India's lead will only increase from here on.
On a length, on off. Shami defends this off the back foot onto the turf. End of a hostile over from Rabada.
BEATEN by the seam movement again! A good-length delivery around off. Shami looks to defend it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
On a length, around off again. Shami defends it tentatively square on the off side.
Good bounce from the length again! A good-length delivery around off. Shami looks to defend it the ball seams away and bounce to hit the top of his blade.
Short ball around leg this time. Shami looks to pull but misses.

FOUR BYES! Ohh..that has beaten everybody!  A good-length delivery around off. Shami looks to defend it but the ball hits the crack and seams away it misses the blade of Shami and De Kock misses it too. The ball races away towards the fence for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! This time Ashwin does not survive the review! It also hit the handle of the bat before hitting the arm guard. Ashwin has to walk back and Rabada gets another wicket. A nasty short one and on middle, this one gets big on Ashwin. He looks to fend it away. It goes off something towards point where Keegan takes it. The finger is raised but Ashwin reviews again. Replays show that there is small spike before the ball hits the arm guard. The umpire feels it has hit the handle and then lobbed to the man at point. The original decision stays. Ashwin is taken by surprise when the umpire yet again signaled out. He was quite confident it hit the arm guard. Also, that was not a short delivery, it was a back of a length ball which just took off.
Commentary.Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Yet another review by Ashwin. He has been given out caught but he reviews.
Back of a length, on off. Pant blocks it off the front foot towards the on side.
Back of a length, on middle. Pant defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Ashwin drives it aerially over mid on and gets a single. Ashwin was struggling at the bowler's end there but Mulder fails to collect the throw cleanly.
Back of a length, on off. Ashwin defends it solidly off the back foot this time.
Mulder goes fuller this time on middle. Ashwin pushes it to mid on.
On a length, on middle. Pant works it behind square on the on side for a single.

FOUR BYES! Salt to the wound after the decision was reversed!  Back of a length and down the leg side. Ashwin looks to clip it away but misses. De Kock behind the stumps misses it too and the ball goes towards the boundary towards long leg.
Review time! Ashwin has been given out caught behind but he reviews. He indicates it is off the arm.

NOT OUT! That is off the bicep and Ashwin survives! Shorter and on off, this keeps rising on the batter. Ashwin stays back and looks to defend. It goes off something to the keeper. South Africa start celebrating. The umpire raises the finger but Ashwin reviews. He indicates it is off the arm. Replays confirm that.
Short ball, on off. Pant pulls it to deep mid-wicket for just a single. Good shot there but just a single.
Back of a length, on middle. Ashwin works it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Ashwin defends this off the back foot towards the off side.

Back of a length, on off. Pant goes on the back foot and punches it through covers. He immediately calls for TWO but decides against it as Bavuma does well to stop it and throw it back quickly. A single taken.
A length ball, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks this one out.
FOUR! A terrific drive by Ashwin! Wiaan Mulder overcooks this delivery, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin drives it beautifully past mid on for a boundary.
Beaten! A length delivery, outside off. Ashwin looks to block that but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Wiaan Mulder goes full again, around the off pole. This is pushed to mid off.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Ashwin lets that go through.
A fuller delivery, on off. Ashwin drives it to mid off. Dot ball.
Length, outside off. Pant leaves that alone. A dot to end the over.
Darting it on the pads this time, on a length. Ravichandran Ashwin tucks it to deep square leg and rotates the strike.
Back of a length, on the body. Pant taps it towards short fine and scampers through to the other end. A single taken.
Short, outside off. Pant offers no shot on that.
Touch short, outside off. Rishabh Pant shoulders arms to it.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Pant defends that with one hand on the leg side.
A single now as this is flicked through square leg.
Back of a length and on middle, defended.

FOUR! That has gone to the fence like a tracer bullet! Shorter and outside off, this is cut through point. This races away to the fence. Temba Bavuma at the backward point jumps to pouch it but it goes over him for another boundary. Pant is a dangerous player and while he is out there, runs will continue to flow.
Back of a length and on off, Pant guides it to point.
FOUR! More runs now! A boundary! Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg. This races across the turf and into the fence.
Add three more to the total! Fuller and on middle, Ashwin strokes it down to long on. Three taken.
Short, on middle. Pant defends this one.
Short again, outside off. Rishabh Pant hangs back and cuts it towards point. The fielder there dives and makes a good stop.
Back of a length, wide of off. Rishabh Pant chops this but manages to get an under edge to cover. He is not quite happy with himself as he could not get hold of this one.
FOUR! Glorious by Pant. Kagiso Rabada changes his length here and goes fuller, outside off. Rishabh Pant leans and drives it through covers for a boundary. Runs are coming quickly here for India.
Swing and a miss! Kagiso Rabada drops it short this time, outside off. Rishabh Pant swings his bat but gets beaten altogether.
A length ball, around off. Rishabh Pant gets an inside edge onto his pads.
FOUR! Oh, shot! Ravichandran Ashwin gets off the mark in style! Marco Jansen overcooks this delivery, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and carves this beautifully over point for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! India have started to tumble here! Marco Jansen picks up yet another wicket and sends Ajinkya Rahane back to the hut now. A short ball, around middle. Ajinkya Rahane goes for the pull shot and gets a big top edge to Rassie van der Dussen at deep square leg. An unnecessary shot by Ajinkya Rahane here, that was not needed. He was looking in good touch but has given it away. India are now 6 down.
Commentary.Howout: c Rassie van der Dussen b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane leaves that alone.
Touch fuller, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane leans and taps it towards cover and scampers through to the other end. Rishabh Pant sends him back. A good call from Pant.
Back of a length, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane hangs back and blocks it to point.
Tad shorter, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Length, outside off. Left alone.

Swing and a miss! Rishabh Pant goes for the big one straight away! Lungi Ngidi serves length delivery, outside off. Rishabh Pant advances down the track and swings his bat hard at it, but gets beaten as the ball zips passes through the outside edge.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Rishabh Pant blocks it out.
A fuller length this time, outside off. Rishabh Pant leans and drives it through covers for a brace. Rishabh Pant gets off the mark with that!
A length ball, outside off. Rishabh Pant leaves that alone.

OUT! India have lost their fifth wicket now! And it is Lungi Ngidi who strikes and sends back Cheteshwar Pujara. He would be disappointed with that dismissal. Lungi Ngidi serves a fuller ball, down the leg side. Cheteshwar Pujara tries to flick but it goes off the inner half. Quinton de Kock makes no mistake and takes it comfortably. Pujara might score a lot of runs of the flick shot but this time he falls. He got off to a start but falls in a very soft manner. Much-needed wicket as the game was slipping away from South Africa.
Commentary.Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary.Commentary: End of a huge over for India! On off, this is blocked.

FOUR! CRACKED! Rahane is in the mood here! What a shot this is! This is slightly fuller and outside off, Rahane creams it through covers. This one races away to the fence in no time. Jansen under huge pressure now.
SIX! Over the fence! Runs flowing now. 100 up for India! Short and on the body, Rahane takes on the challenge of pulling it and clears the fine leg fence.
FOUR! That is a beautiful shot! Boundaries are now coming from time to time! Full and outside off, this is driven through covers for a boundary.
And again, some swing on offer, it comes back in from middle, Rahane works it to mid-wicket.
Some swing but this is down the leg side, Rahane looks to flick but misses.
Yet another delivery outside off, Pujara need not play at those.
Yet another delivery outside off, left alone.
Well adjusted! Length and on off, this one lands and then moves away. Pujara in the end, opens the face of the bat and guides it to point.
Bangs it short, Rahane pulls it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Good length and on off, defended.
A big booming inswinger, comes back in from well outside off. Rahane looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and goes down to fine leg for two.
A shorter one, around middle. Cheteshwar Pujara ducks underneath it.
Oh, dear! Extra bounce there! Marco Jansen serves a length ball, around off. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to block this but misses as the ball takes off the surface and hits the handle of the bat.
Back of a length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it towards mid-on.

FOUR! Change of angle for Marco Jansen and gets hammers for a four! Marco Jansen goes round the wicket this time, serves a full delivery, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara uses his wrists perfectly and pushes it towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone.

FOUR BYES! Some bonus runs for India! Marco Jansen serves a sharp bouncer, outside off. Pujara lets that go through. Quinton de Kock jumps high but fails to grab it. The ball races away to the fence behind the keeper.
On off, defended.
Good length and on off, Rahane pushes it to covers.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! That is a tremendous shot! On the shorter side, outside off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce and plays it through covers. Boundary.
On off, Rahane hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
Slightly fuller and on off, Rahane plays it back to the bowler.
Lungi Ngidi will bowl from the other end.
Another one on the shorter side and angling away. Left alone.
Good length and on off, defended.

Catch it is the cry but it is well away! Shorter and on the body, this is pulled towards fine leg. Lands well away from the fielder. Only one. South Africa have a spring about their step at the moment.
Shorter and on off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce and defends.
Outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Ajinkya Rahane comes to the crease now.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Jansen gets the Indian skipper and this is one wicket he will remember for a long, long time! He is delighted and that is the start South Africa would have wanted after the break. Quite a strange shot though, it is the first ball after a break and to play that shot, really raises questions about what Kohli was thinking. Maybe India had come out with the intent of upping the ante, has backfired though. This is full and quite wide outside off, there to be driven. Kohli goes for it but it finds the outside edge and de Kock does the rest. India are effectively 209 for 4 but South Africa now have a sniff. Also, this is quite similar to the way he gout out in the first innings. Not learning from his mistake is the Indian skipper.
Commentary.Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: We are ready for the post-lunch session. The players are out in the middle. Virat Kohli and Cheteshwar Pujara will resume their innings. Marco Jansen will begin the proceedings. Here we go...
... DAY 4, SESSION 2 ...

For India, they know they are just one partnership away from getting to a lead which is going to be a daunting one. Pujara, after being dropped has looked good. Kohli has also started off well but they need to continue. Also, it will be interesting to see if we see the Indians do up the ante a little after the break. An important session awaits.

A good session for South Africa but have to say, India are still ahead in the game! The hosts really kept it tight. Rabada was excellent at the start. Jansen too supported him well. They got the wicket of Thakur early on and then managed to squeeze. That discipline got about the wicket of Rahul who fell to Ngidi. The home side need to continue this. They can't let India score freely and they have to continue to chip away at the wickets after the break.
Back of a length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Cheteshwar Pujara, on back foot, blocks it out.
On a length, outside off, angling it away this time. Cheteshwar Pujara lets that go through.
Back of a length this time, around the fifth stump. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
Much fuller this time, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it towards cover.
Short and outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara slashes it to point.
A dot to end then! Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Now Kohli bags a boundary through the off side! Shorter in length and outside off, he stands tall and guides it through point. This one races away to the fence.
Another one on the shorter side. Kohli stands tall and blocks.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
Another one outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, left alone.
That might have hurt! On middle, extra bounce. Pujara takes one hand off the handle as he blocks. It might have stung as it hits the higher part of the bat.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shorter and outside off, Pujara stands tall and guides it through point for a boundary.
BEAUTY! This lands on off and then moves away off the wicket. Pujara looks to defend but is beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one on the stumps, defended.
On off, this is blocked.
Fuller this time, around off. Virat Kohli blocks it solidly.
Short in length again, outside off. Virat Kohli leaves it alone.

FOUR and a NO BALL! Top-shot by Virat Kohli! A short ball, wide of off. Virat Kohli, on back foot, opens the face of his bat and guides it past gully for a boundary. And Kagiso Rabada has overstepped again, a no ball called.
Back of a length, outside off. Kohli leans back and leaves that alone.
Review time! It is a review for both, LBW and a catch! Rabada is the man in question and he feels he has his man some way or the other.

NOT OUT! Well, Rabada does not get Kohli but Virat survives by the smallest of margins. That decision could have gone eitherway. A good review by South Africa and they do not lose it too. This is an inswinger, it tails back in from outside off. Kohli looks to flick. It hits the pad for sure and lobs towards point where it is taken. South Africa appeal for both, LBW and a catch. It is turned down. Elgar reviews. Replays show that there is no inside edge and Ball Tracker shows it is clipping the top of leg. Really close.
Touch shorter, wide of off. Virat Kohli lets that go through.
Swinging it away, outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, on a length. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it towards point.
LEG BYE! A length delivery, darting it onto the pads this time. Virat Kohli misses his flick and the ball deflects off his thigh pads and rolls towards short fine leg. The batters steal a leg bye.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Left alone.
A touch fuller, around off. Virat Kohli leans and defends it out.
On a length, outside off. Virat Kohli looks to block again off the front foot, but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Fuller length, outside off. Virat Kohli lunges and blocks it solidly.
Outside off, on a length, swinging it away a tad. Cheteshwar Pujara offers no shot. A maiden over for Kagiso Rabada.
On a length, around middle. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it on the leg side.
Kagiso Rabada serves a sull delivery again, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara leans and drives it to the man at mid ff.
Touch fuller this time, outside the off pole. Left alone.
A length ball again, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards point.
Outside off, on a good length. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, left alone.
Yet another delivery on the stumps, blocked.
FOUR! Tickled fine! On the pads, Kohli shuffles across and works it fine down the leg side. Boundary.
On the stumps, Kohli is solid in defense.
A single now as this is worked through square leg.
On the off pole, Pujara stands tall and keeps it out.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one.
A fuller delivery, outside off. Virat Kohli goes for the drive, but gets an outside edge towards gully.
A length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
A length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli taps it wards point. Virat Kohli wanted the single there, but was sent back by Cheteshwar Pujara.
Outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Clipped away! Angled into the pads, Kohli walks in and then clips it through square leg. This one races away to the fence.
Outside off, left alone.
On the stumps, Pujara pushes it to covers.
Yet another nut outside off, Pujara does not fiddle with it.
On middle, Pujara lunges and keeps it out.
Yet another ball outside off, Pujara does not play at it.
Good length and on off, defended.
Solid! On off, blocked.
Another delivery outside off, Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Outside off, left alone.
Virat Kohli is the new man in, he walks in at number 5.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Rahul falls, that is a loose, loose stroke! He is gutted with himself and rightly so. Very uncharacteristic off him. But maybe him not able to score as freely as he usually does in this innings frustrated him or even the blow earlier on got him rattled. He senses a scoring opportunity here, his eyes probably lit up as he saw width on offer outside off. Rahul slashes but does not do it convincingly. It goes off the outside edge to the man at first slip. Elgar takes an easy catch. This has been really good from South Africa so far. Need to keep going.
Commentary.Howout: c Dean Elgar b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary.Commentary: Outside off, Rahul plays inside the line and lets it be.
A slight halt. KL Rahul has hurt his thumb and the physio is out there to look after it.
That took off! Length and on off, Rahul looks to defend, this one takes off. He does well to take one hand off the handle and hence, it hits the glove and goes along the ground to the slip fielder.
A length ball, around leg. KL Rahul tucks it towards square leg for a single.
A shorter ball, around off, that has just taken off from the surface. KL Rahul bends and lets that go away.
On a length, on middle. KL Rahul pushes it towards mid on.
Full-length delivery, around the fifth stump lime. KL Rahul lunges and gets an outside edge towards gully.
Shaping it in this time, on middle. That has been blocked out by KL Rahul.
Wiaan Mulder drops it short, outside the off pole. KL Rahul, on back foot, pushes it to man at cover.
Touch fuller, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara leans and blocks it on towards point. A dot to end the over.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to square leg.
Tad shorter this time, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara offers no shot on that.
A length delivery, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards point.

A fine drive by KL Rahul! Lungi Ngidi serves an overpitched delivery, on off. KL Rahul, on front foot, drives it past mid off. The ball won't race away all the way, but the batters pick up three runs.
Good-length delivery, around off. KL Rahul leans and blocks it solidly.

DRINKS! South Africa have done well to take an early wicket here, their bowling looks more disciplined. They could have had yet another wicket if Rabada would have held on. They though have done well to not let India score freely and keep the pressure on. However, the visitors are quite ahead, their lead is almost 200 and their cautious approach is probably fine for now.
On off, Pujara pushes it to covers.
Angled into the pads, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
This is even wider outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone nicely.

That is a beauty! This starts on off, it initially seems like it is shaping away but lands and then jags back in. Sneaks between the gap of bat and pad as Pujara tries to defend. Goes over the off pole.
A loosener to begin with. Outside off, left alone.
Another ball on off, Rahul opens the face and plays it to point.
Outside off, Rahul plays inside the line and lets it through.
Better! Drags his length back and also bowls it outside off. Rahul lunges and defends.
FOUR! Ngidi has not started off that well! On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket. It races away to the fence. Lead now 180. 50 up for India.
On off, blocked.
A single now! On middle, this is worked towards fine leg for one.
Another bumper to end, it is ducked under.
Good length and around middle. Rahul blocks it on the leg side.
This one is angled away from the off pole. Left alone.
Back of a length now and on off, Rahul stands tall and blocks.
Almost drags it on! A yorker outside off, Rahul looks to jam it out. It goes off the inner half just wide of the leg pole.
A good bumper, Rahul ducks under it. South Africa have bowled quite a few short ones in this innings. Something they did not in the first.
A dot to end! Outside off, left alone.
Well played! Back of a length and on off, extra bounce. Pujara plays it with soft hands, it goes off the outer half towards third slip where the fielder dives and stops it.

DROPPED! Pujara gets a life! That is the kind of luck a man out of form needs? Rabada the culprit. This is full and on middle, Pujara looks to flick, this stops in the surface. It goes more off the splice towards mid on. Rabada there dives to his left but does not hang on. Two taken. Can Pujara make most of this?
Attacks the stumps this time and on middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Pujara gets off the pair! He will feel really nice! Good shot too to get off the mark. Ngidi starts off with a loosener. Full and on middle, this is whipped down to long on for a boundary.
FOUR! Nicely done! Marco Jansen goes full this time, shaping it onto the pads. KL Rahul flicks it gently towards fine leg for a boundary.
Another back of a length, outside off. KL Rahul, on back foot, taps it towards point again.
A length ball, outside off. KL Rahul blocks it towards point.
Full-length, around middle. KL Rahul pushes it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Tad fuller, drifting it into the pads. KL Rahul misses his flick and gets rapped on the front pad.
Length balll, outside off. Left alone.
Shorter this time, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it out solidly.
Touch fuller, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it back to to the bowler.
Beaten! Good-length delivery, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara goes for the defensive shot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
No ball! Back of a length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it to point again. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped here and a no ball is called.
Full in length, shaping it away outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara guides it towards point.
Length ball, on middle this time. Cheteshwar Pujara taps it on the leg side.
Fuller this time, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara leans and lets that go through.
Good-length delivery, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Marco Jansen getting some extra bounce here! He serves a short delivery again, down the leg side. KL Rahul looks to fend that but the ball whizzes past his arm.
Marco Jansen drops it short again, around off. KL Rahul ducks underneath it and lets that through.
Back of a length, on middle. KL Rahul gets on his toes and blocks it out solidly.
Nipping it back in this time from a good-length, on middle. KL Rahul taps it to the fielder at cover.
Length ball, outside off, swinging it away. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short again, down the leg side again. Cheteshwar Pujara offers no shot on that. End of a successful over.
Cheteshwar Pujara comes to the crease now.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Rabada finally gets the breakthrough! The nightwatchman walks back. Early wicket for South Africa. Rabda has been a lot better, he has made the batter play a lot more and now gets the reward. It is a good length delivery on off, takes off after landing. Thakur looks to defend, it goes more off the higher part of the outside edge and to the third slip fielder. Wiaan Mulder takes it nicely.
Commentary.Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Short in length, outside off. Shardul Thakur shoulders arms to it.
A length delivery, on middle. Shardul Thakur blocks it out off the front foot.
A sharp bouncer again, around middle. Shardul Thakur ducks underneath it.

FOUR BYES! Kagiso Rabada serves a short of length ball, down the leg side. Shardul Thakur misses his pull as the ball swings away from him. Quinton de Kock dives to his left and fails to collect it. The ball races away towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Really good delivery to end! Finally gets it to shape back in nicely, this time it is on off, Rahul gets his front foot out of the way and pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, defended.
Yet again another delivery not on the stumps, easy leave.
Yet another leave! Outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one. They need to make the batsman play a lot more. They have done well so far but need to attack the stumps a lot more.
Yet again outside off, looking for some insward movement, none there and it is an easy leave.
Slightly fuller this time and just outside off, looking for the ball to tail back in. Rahul leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, wide of off. Shardul Thakur offers no short on that.
Back of a length, outside off. Shardul Thakur wanted to play that, but bails out in the end.
Touch fuller again, outside the off pole. Shardul Thakur lets that go through.
Ful-length, outside off. Left alone.
LEG BYE! Nipping back in from a short length. KL Rahul looks to flicks this but, the ball deflects off his thigh pad towards fine leg for a leg bye.
No ball! Short in length again. KL Rahul ducks under it.
Ouch! Kagiso Rabada serves a short ball, around middle. KL Rahul ducks under it, but gets hit on the ribs as the ball fails to bounce. A shout for LBW, but not given.
Short of a length, around off. Shardul Thakur goes to blocks that, but bails out last minute.
A length ball, swinging it on middle. Shardul Thakur leaves that alone, and the ball goes over middle. Once again, left on length.
Beaten! Good-length again, outside off. Shardul Thakur looks to defend that, but gets beaten as the ball zips past through the outside edge once again.
Good-length delivery, wide of off. Shardul Thakur offers no shot on that.
SIX! Bang! That's high and handsome! Marco Jansen serves a short ball, around off. Shardul Thakur hangs back, and plays an upper cut towards deep point for a biggie.
Swing and a miss! Marco Jansen delivers a length ball, outside off. Shardul Thakur goes for the drive but misses as the ball drifts away from him.
Well played in the end! Rabada goes wide of the crease and angles this short one into the body. Rahul initially looks to defend but then pulls his bat back.
Surely some movement for him though! Length and on off, this one moves away. Rahul looks to defend but is beaten.
Shorter in length and on middle, Rahul stands tall and blocks. Not a lot of zip for Rabada so far this morning.
Well wide outside off, Rahul watches it go through to the keeper.
On the fuller side, outside off, Rahul looks to drive, this goes back off the inner half to the bowler.
An awayswinger to begin the over but it is well wide outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Shardul Thakur lets that go through to the keeper.
Review time! That swung back a long way. A huge appeal for an LBW has been turned down. Seems like it is going down leg.

NOT OUT! GOING OVER! Marco Jansen serves a length ball, shaping it into the pads. Shardul Thakur shoulders arms to it, and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW, but the umpire does not raise his finger. Dean Elgar goes for the review. The replays roll in and Ball Tracker confirms the ball was missing the wickets. A little to high here. South Africa lose a review. Thakur probably left that on length.
Good-length delivery, wide of off. Shardul Thakur leaves that alone.
Marco Jansen pulling his length back this time. A shorter delivery, down the leg side. Shardul Thakur goes for the pull but fails to get any bat on it.
A length delivery on this occasion, around middle and leg. Shardul Thakur blocks it out.
Marco Jansen begins with a back of a length ball, wide of off. Shardul Thakur shoulders arms to it.
Who will bowl from the other end? Marco Jansen it is.
Shaping it away this time, length again, outside off. KL Rahul blocks it towards the cover region.
FOUR! In the air... but safe! Kagiso Rabada serves a fuller-length ball, outside off. KL Rahul goes for the drive, but manages to get an outside edge wide of gully for a boundary.
Back of a length, down the leg side. KL Rahul lets that go through.
Beaten! Kagiso Rabada serves a length ball, outside off this time. KL Rahul looks to defend, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tad fuller this time, darting it on the pads again. KL Rahul pushes it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Kagiso Rabada starts off with a length ball, on the pads. KL Rahul flicks it towards mid-wicket.
We are all set for the action to begin! KL Rahul and Shardul Thakur are out in the middle to resume their innings. Kagiso Rabada to bowl the first over. Here we go...

How unpredictable can the Heat be! They almost chased down a massive total of around 200 in their last game and are now reeling at 22 for 4. Switch tabs to catch all the action from the Big Bash League.
The proteas though will know on this wicket, things can change quickly. If they manage to pick a few wickets quickly, they can surely get back into this one. The first session is really important.

India right now is well and truly in the driver’s seat. They have a handsome lead and still have nine wickets in the bag. A couple of good partnerships is all they need to bat South Africa out of the game.

The game moved along at a rapid pace on the so called ‘moving day’. We saw 18 wickets tumble which now makes a result well and truly possible despite all the rain we have had and which is predicted. One believes the wicket is only going to get tougher and we could well be in for another day dominated by the bowlers. Welcome to the coverage of Day 4 of the first Test between India and South Africa.
... DAY 4, SESSION 1 ...

For South Africa, the only way they can get back into the game is by taking wickets. If they manage to pick a few quickly and create panic in the Indian dressing room, you just never know. The new ball will be key, even in the last 30 mins or so, they were quite wayward with their lines and lengths, they’ll need to buck up on Day 4. A fascinating day awaits. Do join us at 1.30 pm IST (8 am GMT) for the first ball but the build-up will begin much in advance. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

The visitors would have loved to enter Day 4 unscathed but they still have 9 wickets in hand and have already added 16 to the lead they had. A couple of partnerships is what they’ll need on Wednesday and they’ll probably be the most likely ones to win this.

Except for the initial phase of the first innings where they collapsed and ended with something below 350, it was all about India. Their bowlers put up an excellent show, Shami, Bumrah, Thakur and Siraj ensured that 327 was well and truly enough and gave India a healthy lead.

A good little passage of play for South Africa comes to an end. They would have desperately wanted a wicket before Stumps and they have got it. However, the day has completely belonged to the Indians and they are in the driver’s seat in this game.

FOUR! Streaky boundary for Shardul Thakur and this will be the end of the day. A good-length delivery around off. Thakur pushes at it tentatively and the ball catches the outside edge of his balde. The ball goes though the gully region and a boundary to end the day for India. India are 16/1 after the end of DAY 3. The lead is now of 146 runs.
Short ball on middle this time. Shardul Thakur ducks under it.
Another good-length delivery around off. Thakur defends this towards the off side cautiously again.
A length ball, on off. Thakur gets forward and defends it towards the off side.
Marco Jansen bowls this hat-trick ball down the leg side. He tries to bowl it straight but just sprays down the leg side a little. Thakur looks to flicks it but misses.
So, India has sent in a nightwatchman. Shardul Thakur has walked out to the middle at No.3.

OUT! TAKEN! De kock certainly had no problems in taking that and Jansen strikes on his first ball. Just what South Africa needed, a widket before Stumps. It is a good length delivery, angling away from off. Agarwal feels for it away from the body. This goes off the outside edge and de Kock takes it. Agarwal is once again found wanting to a ball outside off. He jabs at the delivery which is always risky especially in places like South Africa and England. He got away with a couple earlier on but this time the edge is found. The South Africans are elated. Still time for another and there will be a new kind of energy in this ending phase of Day 3 in the South Africans. Also, he’ll be on a hat-trick. He got the last wicket in the first innings and now strikes on the very first ball.
Commentary.Howout: c Quinton de Kock b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Marco Jansen is brought into the attack.
A short ball to end the over. Rabada bowls this short on middle. KL Rahul ducks under it.
De Kock seems to be struggling a touch! He might have hurt his back in the last over when he dived to catch a ball. He is probably eagerly waiting for Stumps so that he can get some rest.
A good-length delivery on off. Rahul plays it with soft hands towards point.
On a length, on off. Rahul defends this square on the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.
Another good-length delivery outside off. Seaming away with good bounce. Rahul looks to push at it but decides against it at the last moment.
A length ball, outside off. Good away seam movement for Rabada, Rahul pushes at it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.

NO BALL! A short ball and down the leg side. Quinton de Kock fails to collect it cleanly and the batters take a bye. Kagiso Rabada is struggling with his line here. Also, bowls another no ball. Overstepped yet again.
An harmless delivery again. A full ball, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone comfortably.
A length ball, outside off. Seaming away a little. Rahul lets it go again.
A full ball, outside off. Rahul leaves it alone comfortably this time.
A good-length delivery outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone as he mimicks a defensive shot inside the line of the ball.
A short ball on middle this time. Rahul ducks under it without any fuss.
A full ball, on off. Rahul drives it straight to mid on this time.
A length ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends this off the back foot towards the off side.

FOUR! A boundary this time behind square on the off side. A good-length delivery around off. Rabada gets some extra bounce. Mayank Agarwal opens the face of his blade a little and it runs away through gully for a boundary.
Short ball around middle and leg this time. Mayank Agarwal ducks under it.

A fuller ball, on off. Mayank Agarwal doesn't get much forward and the ball hits the inside half of his blade as he looks to defend. It goes towards square leg. South African players got a little excited there.
A length ball, outside off. Mayank Agarwal lets it go carefully.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahul lets it go this time. Rahul is looking solid here.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul gets back and defends it. The ball hits the top of his blade and goes towards the off side.
FOUR! Good shot! Back of a length, outside off. Rahul gets on the top of the ball and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Another fuller delivery and wider outside off. Rahul leaves it alone comfortably this time. He needs to make batter play here.
A fuller delivery outside off. Some swing there for Ngidi as Rahul leaves it alone.
On a good-length, on off. Rahul defends this off the front foot with soft hands towards the off side.
Lungi Ngidi to bowl from the opposite end.
Another good-length delivery outside off with good carry. Mayank Agarwal rides the bounce and pushes it square on the off side.
On a length and seaming away. Agarwal defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
On a length, on off. Agarwal works it to the on side this time.
Ohh...Good bounce and carry for Rabada! A good-length delivery, around off. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend it off the back foot but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
A length ball, on middle this time. Mayank Agarwal works it to mid-wicket this time.
A good-length delivery outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
NO BALL! Kagiso Rabada starts with a good-length ball, on off. Rahul plays it well with soft hands towards backward point for a single. He is off the mark. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped.

That’s it from this Test then! It is India who have taken a 1-0 lead and now have a chance to create history in the next Test. A win will see them win a Test series for the very first time in South Africa. The hosts, on the other hand, need to avoid a defeat to stay in the series. The second Test starts on the 3rd of January at 1:30 pm IST (8 am GMT). See you then and a Happy New Year in advance!

KL Rahul is the PLAYER OF THE MATCH for his brilliant knock in the first innings! He says that it was about grit and determination and the opening partnership was crucial. He added that they set the tone for the team. He adds that he did not make many technical changes but it is more about mental space and remaining calm. He mentions that the discipline he has shown is the biggest contributor to perform consistently. He adds that he is proud of his overseas performance. He applauds Shami and the bowling group for their consistent performances in different situations over the years. He adds that it is a special win and they want to build on this and get better and try to win another Test in a few days time.

Virat Kohli, the Indian skipper, says that getting a result in four days shows how much this team was motivated to get a win at Centurion against South Africa. Adds that the discipline shown by the batters showed in the first innings is praiseworthy. Praises Agarwal and Rahul for the way they laid the platform and put them on top. Says that he knew that the bowlers would get the wickets. Says that if Bumrah hadn't been injured in the first innings, the game would have probably been over earlier than this. Credits the bowlers not just for this Test but for how Indian Test cricket has progressed over the years. He Praises Shami for the way he bowled and says that he is one of the best pacers going around in world cricket. Mentions that their show in Wanderers in 2018 showed their grit and determination so they are looking forward to playing the second game there.

Dean Elgar, the skipper of South Africa, says that there are a lot of positives still and credits India for bowling really well and keeping them on their toes. Mentions that if they could have batted better and then, it might have given them a chance to win this match. Tells that the bowlers bowled really well on Day 3 and executed the right lines and lengths. States that they fought back hard with the ball in the second innings. Adds that they need to improve their batting as it was the main reason that they lost this match. Also says that he will sit along with the management and discuss strategies. Tells that they didn't do a lot of things wrong and it is not all doom and gloom for them. Ends by saying that they strive under pressure and that is a positive sign.
Stay tuned for the presentation.

South Africa were in the game till Elgar was batting. The skipper led the fightback and kept his sides’ hopes alive. He though failed to receive support from the others as Shami and Bumrah were too hot to handle for the rest. In the end, it is a convincing win for the visitors and it is also their FIRST IN CENTURION IN TESTS!

The South African bowlers though roared back on Day 4 as they bundled India for below 200. Jansen and Rabada were the stars. They gave their side a chance, a small chance as they had to chase down something just over 300.

That though proved to be well and truly enough as the Indian pacers, led by Shami, who got a fifer, helped India take a lead of over 100 runs. Also, the lead could have been a lot more had Bumrah got more overs under his belt. He was injured for the most part but the others stepped up brilliantly.
There was no cricket on Day 2 but South Africa came back strongly on Day 3. India were eyeing over 400 but Ngidi and Rabada ensured they kept them below the 350-run mark.

Also, we had one full day being washed out due to rain, despite that, it was quite a convincing one. Right from Day 1, they were well and truly on top of the game. They won the toss elected to bat and courtesy a ton from Rahul and decent performances from Agarwal and Rahane, India finished strongly on the first day.

If there are two places where visiting sides find it difficult to win, it is the Gabba in Australia and it is Centurion here in South Africa and India have managed to win in both. That speaks volumes about how good a side they are.

OUT! TAKEN! All over! Victory for India in Centurion! Flatter and on middle. Ngidi looks to block it with hard hands and gets the inside edge. The ball goes straight to leg slip and Cheteshwar Pujara takes it with ease! Centurion has been conquered by India as they win by 113 runs!
Commentary.Howout: c Cheteshwar Pujara b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: Lungi Ngidi is the last man in.

OUT! TAKEN! 9 down now South Africa! Well bowled by Ashwin. He tosses it nicely, wide outside off. Rabada looks to drive but does so with his hands reaching out. The ball takes the outside edge and loops up towards point. Mohammed Shami takes an easy catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Mohammed Shami b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: Loopy ball, outside off. Rabada looks to drive but gets the outside edge to covers.
Flatter ball, outside off. Rabada blocks it out.
Darted on the pads. Bavuma works it to deep square leg for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Kagiso Rabada is the next batter in.

OUT! TAKEN! Shami strikes right after Lunch and Marco Jansen's stay ends! That is a peach of a delivery to any batter let alone a tailender. Length ball, just outside off. Jansen is tentative in his push forward to block it but gets the outside edge. Pant dives to his right and takes the catch. A brilliant start for India post Lunch and a couple of wicket-taking deliveries now will give them a 1-0 lead in the series!
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: Beaten! On a length, just outside off. Jansen pokes his bat out but the ball goes past the outside edge.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Oh, that is glorious! Full and on off. Jansen drives it nicely past mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! Through the slips! Length and outside off. Jansen looks to block but gets the outside edge past third slip for a boundary.
We are all set for the Post-Lunch session! The Indian players are out there in the huddle. Temba Bavuma and Marco Jansen will resume for South Africa. Mohammed Shami to start for India. Here we go...
... DAY 5, SESSION 2 …

Now then. We have 2 more sessions to go but, but there is rain expected after the second session and if that happens while South Africa are still batting, then anything can happen. Bavuma has looked really good in the middle and South Africa would want him to bat as long as possible while praying for some help from the rain gods. What will happen? Do join us at 4:10 pm IST (10:40 am GMT) for what could be the last session of the game!

Patience was the name of the game for India. The first half-hour of play did not go their way but they did not lose their cool. They stuck to their plans and got help from a Day-5 pitch. The wicket of Elgar was the opening they needed and then the pacers were relentless. Bumrah, Siraj and Shami all took a wicket each as India are a few wicket-taking deliveries away from a victory here.

The day started with Bavuma and Elgar looking very comfortable for the first 30 minutes. Boundaries were coming along nicely and Elgar was even dropped once by Shami. It looked like as the ball got older, South Africa were getting more and more comfortable in the middle. But, in situations like these, a wicket can turn things around quite quickly and the wicket of Elgar did just that. Once their skipper fell, the middle order of South Africa was under a lot of pressure. De Kock was very jittery during his stay in the middle and lost his wicket soon. What could have been a good session for South Africa after what was a solid start to the day, ended up being a tough session for them taking the hosts closer to a defeat.
A brilliant session for India and the writing is pretty much on the wall now. The visitors are just 3 wickets away from a historic win here.

Tossed up delivery on off by Ashwin to end the session. Bavma safely defends it towards the off side. Bavuma is solid as rock in the middle and he will be crucial for South Africa going forward. South Africa are 182/7 at Lunch on Day 5.
Tossed up again, around middle and leg. Defended towards the on side. There was a bit of drift and turn for Ashwin there.
Nicely tossed up on off by Ashwin. Bavuma is right forward and defends it solidly.
A fuller delivery on middle. Bavuma blocks it out towards the on side.
Shorter length on off. Bavuma pushes this to covers off the back foot.
Tossed up on middle. Bavuma pushes this towards the on side. The fielder at short deep mid-wicket dives and stops it.
A short ball on middle to end the over. Jansen ducks under it.
Shami goes fuller this time on middle. Bavuma drives it to right of mid on and gets a single.
Back of a length, on off. Jansen pushes this off the back foot to covers and gets a single.
On a length and nipping into middle. Bavuma pushes this off the inside half of his blade to deep mid-wicket for one.
Good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone comfortably.
On a length, on off. Temba Bavuma defends it out.
On middle, Bavuma works it through mid-wicket and takes one.
Flighted delivery and on off, Bavuma blocks.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Bavuma plays it to covers.
On middle, Bavuma pushes it towards short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Just timed it and the outfield here is really quick. On off, a little too full. Bavuma strokes it through covers. Siraj runs after it and dives but in vain.
A yorker from Ashwin on middle, Bavuma jams it out.
Yet another length ball and on off, blocked.
FOUR! Shot! That went to the fence in no time! A full ball outside off, Jansen hits it nicely through covers and this one races away. This guy can bat.

Almost jinxed it! Shorter and outside off, this one comes back in. Bavuma looks to push it on the off side, he gets an inside edge which lands just wide of the off pole. A single as it rolls on the leg side.
FOUR! Classy from Bavuma! Shorter and on off, Bavuma stands tall and pushes it through covers. He looked South Africa's best batter in the first innings and is playing really well again here.
Solid! Good length and on middle, Bavuma plays it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, Bavuma looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on off, defended back to the bowler. Siraj once again walks upto Bavuma and says sorry. He just knows what he did was not needed. Good from the young pacer.

Bavuma has been hit by Siraj here! Bavuma plays the shot straight to Siraj. Siraj collects it and fires in a throw at the batter's end. It was unnecessary to say the least. Bavuma was well inside his crease and the throw has hit him on the foot. He looks in some pain and is getting some treatment now. Bavuma is fine now and is ready to go.

OUCH! That would have really hurt! That was not needed from Siraj. He does apologize but that is really not needed. On middle, this is played back to the bowler. Siraj collects it and then has a shy at the stumps at the keeper's end but hits the foot of the batter. Bavuma is in pain.
Extra bounce! Length and on middle, Jansen looks to defend, this one takes off. It goes off the handle towards the leg side.
Angles it into the middle pole, Jansen defends it solidly.
A short one now and on off, Jansen picks it early and ducks under it.
Hits the length hard and bowls it on off, Jansen plays it towards cover.
Marco Jansen is the next batter in.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Shami comes on and Shami strikes! Mulder falls for just the one run. India just the three wickets away now. Shami lands it on a length, this pitches and then moves away slightly. Mulder lunges and tries to block. He actually ends up pushing at it away from the body. A faint edge and Pant does the rest. India can surely sense a win before Lunch here.
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: On middle, Mulder defends it nicely.
Mohammed Shami (13-2-43-1) is back into the attack.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter in length and outside off, Bavuma shoulders arms to this one.
A gift for Mulder first up but he fails to put it away! A full toss on the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Wiaan Mulder is the next batter in.

OUT! CHOPS IT ON! This was on the cards. This was so on the cards. If you remember Siraj's last over, just visualize 57.2 and 57.3. De Kock could have been dismissed on either ball, once getting an inside edge onto his pad and once, being beaten on the inside edge. In fact, we could hear Kohli saying there it is just a matter of time that is because de Kock has played 18 balls but has looked a little shaky. Well, it has not taken long at all. De Kock looked fidgety all this while, he was looking to play way too many shots and in the end picks the wrong ball to play the wrong shot yet again and falls. Also, this is almost a carbon copy of the way he got out in the first innings. Once again de Kock looks to cut a ball outside off. It is too close to play that shot. He gets an underedge and it crashes into the stumps. Huge wicket as de Kock could have really taken the game away from India. Poor from de Kock though. He could have played with a lot more responsibility. India just 4 wickets away now.
Commentary.Howout: b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary.Commentary: Confusion but safe! On off, de Kock drops it towards cover, then calls for a run but then sends his parnter back in time. Just sense there is a wicket around the corner. De Kock is really looking shaky.
Short and well wide outside off, de Kock slashes but misses. Missing quite a few bad balls is de Kock. This will only frustrate him.
A single to end! Outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Half an appeal, first for a caught behind and then for stumping. Both not given. De Kock would feel he missed out again. Shorter and down the leg side. De Kock looks to pull but misses.
De Kock misses out! A full toss outside off, de Kock drives but straight to covers.
On the pads, Bavuma works it through mid-wicket for one. Not sure about the line bowled by Ashwin. It is more on the leg pole. A little negative.
Tossed up on middle, Temba plays it to mid on.

Risky shot and a risky run too! Both come off! This one drifts in from outside off, de Kock still manages to guide it past point. Too close to play that shot but still gets it towards the fielder there. They take one. Pant is not happy as he feels a single was not on there.
A single to end! Outside off, de Kock guides it past point for one.
Angled into the pads, Bavuma works it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.

Bavuma saves a certain boundary there! This is fuller and on middle, de Kock drives it crisply towards Bavuma at the other end. Bavuma probably is on the go for a one but then realises the ball is coming back to him. Fails to get out in time, it hits him and goes towards mid off for one.
Almost chops it on! Looking to play far too many shots is de Kock! Shorter and just outside off, not enough room to cut. De Kock slashes but misses.

You can hear Kohli saying there it is just a matter of time that is because de Kock has played 18 balls but has looked a little shaky. He is looking to score freely which could be dangerous. This is angled into the pads, de Kock looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Uppish but wide! Risky shot that. He looks to drive this length ball on the up through extra cover. It holds its line, goes more off the outer half uppishly but wide of cover for two.
Flatter ball, lands on off and comes back in. Bavuma blocks it away.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. De Kock sweeps but gets the inside edge to fine leg for one.
Loopy ball, outside off. Bavuma pushes it past cover for one.
Darted on the pads. Swept away for a single by de Kock.
Flatter ball, on middle and leg. De Kock looks to reverse sweep but gets hit on the pads.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.
Ravichandran Ashwin (4-1-6-0) is back into the attack.
A short one to end! Comes quite slow off the deck. Bavuma ducks under.
Yet another nut well outside off, Bavuma shoulders arms to this one.
Well wide outside off, Bavuma need not play at those.
This one comes back in from outside off, not enough though to make the batter play.
Angles this into the off pole from wide of the crease. Defended solidly.
Two more! Fuller and outside off, Bavuma drives, it is a mere push actually through covers for two. 150 up. A little more than 150 needed now. Long way to go.

FOUR! That is beautiful! Lovely timing! Conseuctive boundaries and this one, a lot better than the last. Fuller and on middle, de Kock once again shows the maker's name and plays it past mid on. Races away.
FOUR! Bumrah goes for the yorker but ends up serving a gift, a full toss on middle, de Kock just uses the pace, shows the full face of the bat and plays it through mid on for a boundary.
Soft leading edge! Angled into the pads, de Kock looks to work it on the leg side. Closes the face of the bat early, it goes off the leading edge on the off side.
Length again and on off, de Kock pushes it to mid off.
Now bowls it on a length and outside off, extra effort in that delivery. Left alone.
Quite wristy! Angled into the middle, de Kock works it with the angle through square leg. Wants two, gets two.

Drinks! A classic first hour of Test cricket this. Both teams fighting hard and India have inched ahead with the wicket of South African skipper Dean Elgar. Indian bowlers are bowling good lines and lengths and there is enough help from the wicket for them. For South Africa, this pair of Bavuma and Quinton de Kock will be crucial. Can India get one of them early post Drinks?
Full and outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it to extra cover.
FOUR! Off the edge! Good-length ball, around off. Temba Bavuma stands up on his toes and looks to punch. The ball goes off the outside edge past the third slip fielder for a boundary.
Switches to over the wicket now, bowls it on a length, on middle. Quinton de Kock flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Quinton de Kock drives but straight to the man at covers.
Length ball, outside off. Quinton de Kock cuts it past point for a couple of runs. He likes scoring square on the off side.
On a length, on off. Quinton de Kock stays solid in his defence.
Outside off, Bavuma with an easy leave.
Lots of oohs and ahhs from the Indians behind the stumps. On a good length, angling in, around off. Temba Bavuma watches the ball closely and shoulders arms.
On a good length, on middle. Temba Bavuma defends it towards covers.
Fuller, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, on off. Temba Bavuma pushes it to mid off.
Well bowled! On a good length, angling in, on off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Fuller, on off. Quinton de Kock watchfully blocks it out.
On a length, on middle. Temba Bavuma tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Temba Bavuma sits under it.
Coming in with the angle, on off. Temba Bavuma stays solid in his defence.
Outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone.
On a good length, on off. Temba Bavuma stands tall and defends it to the off side.
Good-length ball, around off. Straightens up after pitching. Quinton de Kock looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Quinton de Kock is the next batter in.

Review! Dean Elgar has been given LBW here! He reviews it. It looks dead straight! The UltraEdge shows that there is not bat involved. Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows THREE REDS and Dean Elgar departs! Big wicket for India.

OUT! LBW! There's the breakthrough! India desperately needed the wicket of Dean Elgar and they have got it. So often we have seen that whenever India are in search for a wicket, Jasprit Bumrah steps up and gets one for his team. Yesterday, got the wicket of the nightwatchman, Keshav Maharaj at the stroke of Stumps and now removes the man who was holding the key for South Africa. Coming to the ball, it was a good-length ball, on middle, angling in. Dean Elgar shuffles across a bit and looks to clip it on the leg side. But he misses and gets rapped on the pads. Jasprit Bumrah and Co. appeal strongly and the umpire raises his finger. Dean Elgar opts for a review though. UltraEdge shows that there was no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows that the ball was pitching outside off, impact was in line and it was hitting the stumps. Jasprit Bumrah has got the better of Dean Elgar in both the innings and his resilience comes to an end. India have got the opening now.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller this time, on off. Dean Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Dean Elgar stands up on his toes and blocks it out.
Good-length ball, in the fifth stump channel. Dean Elgar watches the ball closely and makes a good leave.
On a good length, outside off. Dean Elgar lets it sail through.
On a length, on off. Bavuma solidly defends this from his crease towards the off side.
A fuller delivery by Siraj on middle. Elgar clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Good-length delivery around off. Elgar defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off from Siraj. Elgar pushes this off the back foot towards the off side.
Nice timing from Bavuma! Back of a length, on off. Bavuma punches this off the back foot through covers. Rahul running behind it stops it with a slide near the fence. Three runs taken.
Good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone this time.
Mohammed Siraj (11-4-25-1) comes into the attack.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Short ball this time angling into the body from 'round the wicket. Elgar ducks under it.
A good-length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
FOUR! Another boundary for Elgar! Bumrah sprays this on the pads. Elgar stays deep in his crease and flicks it through square leg for a boundary. Good shot.
A length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.

FOUR! Genuine edge but falls in the gap and goes for a boundary. A good-length delivery around off. Elgar pushes forward to defend, the ball seams away a little. It catches the outside edge of his blade and flies towards the vacant third slip area for a boundary.
Good-length delivery on off this time. Bavuma defends it solidly towards the off side.
A fuller ball, on middle. Bavuma drives it towards short mid on. He half-stops it and the ball goes behind the bowler's end.
A length ball, targeted on the stumps again. Bavuma defends it off the back foot. The ball hits high on his blade.
Good-length delivery on middle and seaming in a little this time. Bavuma drives it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Bavuma defends it carefully towards short cover.
Drifting on the pads this time. Elgar flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
This one hits the crack and seams away! A good-length delivery outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone as the ball seams away sharply.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone. Good carry there for Bumrah.
Back of a length again on middle. Bavuma again solidly defends this towards the on side.
Back of a length, on off. Bavuma is right behind it and blocks it.
Good-length delivery around off this time. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on middle. Worked passed square leg for a couple by Bavuma.

FOUR! This time a boundary! A good-length delivery around off. Elgar pushes at it with soft hands and gets a thick outside edge. The ball races through the gap and for a boundary towards third man. That is insult to injury for Shami.
A bouncer this time down the leg side by Shami. Elgar ducks under it.

Ohh...DROPPED! Shami drops this off his own bowling. A big miss for India! On a length, on off. Elgar pushes this aerially straight to Shami. He drops it. This can prove very costly for India. Big opportunity missed given that it is the set man who has been put down here.
On a length, on off. Bavuma defends it towards the on side and gets a quick single. Good running.
Good-length delivery around off. Bavuma lets it go this time.
Shami bowls this fuller on off. Bavuma drives it to mid off. Indian bowlers are not finding the movement they found on Day 4.
Back of a length, around off. Tapped to cover.
Bumrah wants Elgar to drive as he keeps slanting it away from the off pole but the South African skipper leaves it.
Another one angling across off and another leave by Elgar.
Full and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Length and on the pads. Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Bumrah bowls a length ball, down the leg side. Elgar helps it on its way towards fine leg and even a dive by Shardul Thakur cannot stop the ball.
Shami slips a full one, on middle now but Bavuma blocks it with ease.
Nice and full, just outside off. Driven nicely to mid off.
Short of a length, on off. Bavuma blocks it from the crease.
Fuller and on the pads. Elgar flicks it past mid-wicket to get a single. The hosts now need 199 to win this Test.
Shami digs this short, outside off. Elgar leaves this one alone.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Bumrah ends the over with a length ball, on off and Bavuma has a solid defence to offer.
Length ball, but wide enough for Bavuma to leave it with ease.
A touch shorter, on off. Bavuma stays in the crease and taps this out.
FOUR! That is a glorious stroke! A touch overpitched, outside off. Bavuma plants his front foot forward and gets his head over the ball to drive it gloriously through covers.
Fuller and just outside off. Bavuma shoulders his arms.
Lands on a length, outside off and comes back in. Bavuma leaves it alone.
Jasprit Bumrah to continue.
On a length, around off. Blocked out.
Shami goes back to bowling outside off and Elgar leaves it.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shami errs and bowls a full one, on the pads. Elgar nicely flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Left alone again by Elgar.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.

Length ball, just outside off. Elgar is a bit tentative in his block and gets the outside edge. It goes past point and the batters sprint back for the second. Oh well, it is called a no ball as Shami has overstepped.
Mohammed Shami to bowl now.
Shami serves a full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Bumrah starts with a length ball, on the pads. Bavuma is solid as he taps it towards mid-wicket.

We are set to begin! Indian players stride out to the middle. All eyes will be on Dean Elgar who holds the key for South Africa. He is accompanied by Temba Bavuma. Jasprit Bumrah will complete his over.

COVID UPDATE - Yes, unfortunately, that has to be the title. We are getting multiple quantities of bad news from Australia. First, a staff member of the Melbourne Stars, a team in the Big Bash League, Australia's domestic T20 League, tested positive for Covid and the game which was supposed to be held today got postponed. Minutes later, we received this news that the assigned match referee for the Ashes series - David Boon - has tested positive as well and will miss the 4th Ashes Test in Sydney. He will be replaced by Steve Bernard. Hope that both the affected people recover quickly.

India on the other hand, need to continue what they have done so far in the game. They will know if they hit the right lines and lengths on this wicket, there’s always a ball with the batter’s name on it. To ease their nerves though, they would love an early wicket. An important first session coming up.

The task is still big one ahead of the hosts! They would have loved to have entered Day 5 with just the two wickets down. However, a lot will depend on the likes of Bavuma, de Kock and Elgar. Their skipper is well set but it’s a new day and he really needs to play a big knock here. Also, he’ll have to hope someone sticks around with him. Will the Proteas show some fight, some character?

The equation is quite simple -  India need another 6 wickets to win, South Africa have to score another 211 runs and both the teams will have around 98 overs, weather permitting that is, to do so. First though, let me give you some good news to begin with, it is currently not raining and the forecast has improved so we are surely going to begin on time. Welcome to the coverage.
... DAY 5, SESSION 1 ...

Now, for the hosts, a lot will depend on their skipper, Bavuma and de Kock, they need to come to the fore. For, India, it is about being disciplined. If you just hit the right lines and lengths on the wicket, one will be rewarded. However, the forecast is not the best for Thursday. Let’s hope rain does not play spoil sport as Day 5 promises to be an exciting one. Do join us at 1.30 pm IST (8 am GMT). But the build-up will begin much in advance. Till then, see ya!

Earlier in the day, India opted for a cautious approach in the first session but then looked to up the ante in the second. They did manage to score quickly but also lost wickets. In the end, they managed to get the lead above 300 before being bowled out. They gave themselves just over a session on Day 4 to bowl at the South African batters and they have got 4 important wickets.

The final session was a really good one. It began with Siraj getting rid of Keegan. Rassie and Elgar then showed great character and put up a fighting stand. Just as it seemed that South Africa might start Day 5 with 8 wickets in hand, Bumrah came to the fore for India. He got two wickets right at the end and has turned the tide in India’s favour yet again.

A wicket right at the end means this session belongs to the visitors and they will be pretty pleased with the shift put in by them. Credit though to South Africa too, they fought hard, they showed great character, especially their skipper Elgar but despite that, they still have mammoth task ahead of them.

OUT! TIMBER! BOOM BOOM BUMRAH! Just when the nightwatchman was looking solid, Jasprit Bumrah finds a way to get rid of him. What a bowler. Outsanding stuff. Bowls a toe-crushing yorker, on leg, angling in from outside off. Keshav Maharaj couldn't do anything there. He clears his front leg and tries to squeeze it out but the ball was too quick. Before he could bring his bat down, the ball sneaks and rattles the stumps behind. The nightwatchman departs. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Commentary.Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Good-length ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj defends it out.

FOUR! Fine shot! Back of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj punches it off the back foot through covers. This time the ball races away to the fence. Kind of a shot a top-order batsman would play. The nightwatchan is really looking solid.
Good-length ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj punches it through covers for a brace.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.

LEG BYE! A shout for LBW, but umpire is not interested in that. A length ball, on the pads. Keshav Maharaj misses his flick and gets rapped on the pads. The ball deflects off the pads and rolls towards fine leg. The batters steal a leg bye.

A fuller delivery again, on middle. Keshav Maharaj lunges and tries to block it. The ball gets the outer half of the bat and rolls towards mid off. A slight fumble there allows the batters to take a single.
Fuller length, around middle. Keshav Maharaj leans and blocks it out.
Yorker length, on off. Keshav Maharaj jams it out.
Touch shorter this time, wide of off. Dean Elgar chops it past the gully fielder for a single.

FOUR! And that's fifty for Dean Elgar! Mohammed Siraj serves a length ball, on the pads. Dean Elgar uses his wrists and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary! 50 for the South African captain, a well-composed innings by him. His 18th Test fifty. It has been a knock of patience and grit from the skipper.
Back of a length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj defends but gets the inside half of his blade. The ball rolls towards backward square leg.
A short ball from 'round the wicket on the body. Keshav Maharaj rides the bounce and defends it towards the on side.
NO BALL! Ohh..A beamer from Bumrah! Thankfully Keshav Maharaj tackled it well. It is on off. Keshav Maharaj sways away from the line of the ball. Jasprit Bumrah immediately apologises.
Back of a length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj is hurried by that ball but defends it out in the end.
A full ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj gets his bat down in time as that keeps low again.
Back of a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj plays inside the line of the ball. Bumrah needs to make him play here.
A full ball on off from Bumrah. Keshav Maharaj defends this off the front foot.
A full ball, on middle. Elgar flicks it to deep square leg and decides against taking a single. He wants to protect himself against Bumrah.
Good-length delivery on off. Elgar defends it to the off side this time. Good bowling by Siraj.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar hops and defends it towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar pushes it off the back foot to mid on.
FOUR! A slower short ball, outside off. The ball almost stops before it reaches Elgar. Elgar waits for it and then cuts it through covers for a boundary.
Beaten! A full ball,on off. Elgar looks to drive it but gets beaten. This is beautiful bowling from Siraj.
Short delivery on off to end the over. Keshav Maharaj ducks under it.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
NO BALL! Good-length delivery outside off. Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone. No ball called as Jasprit Bumrah overstepped.
South Africa has sent in a nightwatchman. Keshav Maharaj walks out to bat.

OUT! BOWLED! Jasprit Bumrah is the man for India. He strikes yet again when the team needed it the most. A good-length delivery around off. Rassie van der Dussen decides to play safe and tries to leave it. But the ball nips in sharply to shatter his off-stump. A big wicket for India and this is the breakthrough they needed. Rassie fought hard till he was there but his team needed him to stay longer. Not sure though why Rassie left that. Bumrah, with his unusual style of bowling normally gets the ball to come back in. This wasn’t far enough to leave, maybe he thought it would be going away. Big mistake by Rassie. India surely have time for another wicket. Nervous period for South Africa now.

The on-air commentators are discussing this worldwide problem of overstepping, which seems to be spreading like a rage in Test matches. We saw this during the ongoing Ashes as well. So the reason for this, is opined as lack of practice of run up during the nets. Yes, practice of run up. Many fast bowlers do not pay attention to this small fact and just run in and bowl in the nets. But the commentators suggest that if you just pay attention to these small facets - for example, have someone help you to mark your runup and ensure you are not overstepping - it could bring a lot of discipline into bowling. What many bowlers do not realize is - in the aim to stop the issue of no balls during a match, they start adjusting their runups during a match and end up losing focus from the primary objective - line and length. Well, as they say, practice makes one perfect!

Kohli was even heard saying that if Mayank's was out in the first innings, this is plumb, that is not the case though as it is clipping the top of the stumps. Really close.

For India, it is all going according to the plan, they came out with intent and attacked the South African bowlers earlier in the session. Yes, they did keep losing wickets but have managed to take the lead past the 300-run mark. They then had a little time to bowl at South Africa before the break and they have managed to get the important wicket of Markram. The wicket has a lot on offer and it is all about being patient and hitting the right lines and that is what India have done in this Test. Can they continue the good work? We will find out in the final session. We will be back at 7.00 pm IST (1.30 pm GMT). Stay tuned.

South Africa have done well to only lose the single wicket in the little time they had before the break because the Indian bowlers were right on the money again! Both Shami and Bumrah bowled relentless lines and lengths and tested the South African batters. They got the big wicket of Markram courtesy Shami but Elgar and Keegan have shown very good fight to ensure there were no more wickets to fall after that. Still a long way to go though and the hosts will hope the two can keep fighting.
